    {
      "index": "41",
      "number": "10",
      "title": "Trivia",
      "html": "<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Trivia\">Trivia</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>If the starter home is not converted into an entryway, and the double bed in the upstairs main hall is built, then the unused bed will be used by a character. The room will also feature a hanging rack, and firepit.\n<ul><li>If the starter home <i>is</i> converted into an entryway, the wall shelves and the tall shelf with the display case will be transferred to the west bedroom in the main hall, the square table and chairs will be moved to below the stairs along the west wing, and the double bed will be transferred to the east bedroom in the main hall. However, the firepit, hanging rack, and satchel on the corresponding wall shelf will disappear. All other furnishings will stay put.</li></ul></li>\n<li>The Dragonborn can pay the steward to deal with the furnishings process, and the furnishings will appear in their respective rooms over time. The cost to upgrade each room is:\n<ul><li>Small House: 1,000 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Entry Room Upgrade: 1,000 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Main Hall: 3,500 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Library: 1,500 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Trophy Room: 1,500 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Bedrooms: 2,000 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Greenhouse: 1,500 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Enchanter's Tower: 2,500 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Alchemy Laboratory: 2,500 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Armory: 2,000 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Storage Room: 1,000 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span></li>\n<li>Kitchen: 1,500 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span>\n<ul><li>The exception is the Cellar, which requires all furnishings to be built manually.</li></ul></li></ul></li>\n<li>The Dragonborn can ask their Steward where to purchase building materials, such as <a href=\"/wiki/Straw\" class=\"mw-disambig\" title=\"Straw\">Straw</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Glass_(Hearthfire)\" title=\"Glass (Hearthfire)\">Glass</a>, and the Steward will give them directions to the nearest general goods store. They can also pay their Steward 200 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span> for 20 <a href=\"/wiki/Sawn_Log\" title=\"Sawn Log\">Sawn Logs</a>, 100 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span> for 20 <a href=\"/wiki/Quarried_Stone\" title=\"Quarried Stone\">Quarried Stone</a>, and 20 <span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/Septim_(Coin)\" title=\"Gold\"><img alt=\"Gold\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-image-key=\"GoldIcon.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/elderscrolls/images/8/8a/GoldIcon.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/20?cb=20120214050859\" /></a></span> for 20 <a href=\"/wiki/Clay\" title=\"Clay\">Clay</a>.</li>\n<li>There is no Homestead available in <a href=\"/wiki/Winterhold_(Skyrim_Hold)\" title=\"Winterhold (Skyrim Hold)\">Winterhold</a>, regardless if <i>Hearthfire</i> is installed or not. In addition, there are no housecarls, bards, stewards, or carriage drivers available in said Hold. It also does not matter if <a href=\"/wiki/Korir\" title=\"Korir\">Korir</a>'s quest to retrieve the <a href=\"/wiki/Helm_of_Winterhold\" title=\"Helm of Winterhold\">Helm of Winterhold</a> is complete.</li>\n<li>The music that plays inside of each Homestead is the same music that plays in walled cities, such as <a href=\"/wiki/Whiterun_(Skyrim)\" title=\"Whiterun (Skyrim)\">Whiterun</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Solitude_(Skyrim)\" title=\"Solitude (Skyrim)\">Solitude</a>.</li>\n<li>The exterior chest outside of each Homestead is safe for storage, and does not respawn.</li>\n<li>Unlike regular carriage drivers, the ones at homesteads are free, and have more destination options.</li>\n<li>It is recommended to remove heavy clutter before starting construction, or the Dragonborn can quickly be overencumbered due to their crafting equipment.</li>\n<li>The wings, Cellar, and exterior decorations do not need to be built in the order listed above. The exterior decorations can be built before the Main Hall is drafted, and the Cellar can be finished before any wings are built.</li>\n<li>Once all available options on a drafting table or carpenter's workbench are selected, the corresponding table can be removed.</li>\n<li>The bedroom addition converts two child beds to single beds, which can be used by characters along with the unused double bed. This allows the housecarl, steward, and bard to have normal sleep cycles. Useful for adding dreams to the <a href=\"/wiki/Skull_of_Corruption_(Skyrim)\" title=\"Skull of Corruption (Skyrim)\">Skull of Corruption</a>, using the <a href=\"/wiki/Pickpocket\" title=\"Pickpocket\">Night Thief</a> perk, feeding as a <a href=\"/wiki/Vampire_(Skyrim)\" title=\"Vampire (Skyrim)\">Vampire</a>, or keeping all characters safe from random encounters upon arriving at night. Furthermore, if the bed is kept in the starter home a follower can be commanded to use it, adding another dream charge, or blood bank to the home.\n<ul><li>Unless the family is living in a particular home, all beds can be used by the characters present there. This allows dream gathering, pickpocketing, and vampiric feedings to occur at the unused homes as well.</li></ul></li>\n<li>If the Bedrooms wing is selected, both child's beds and child's chests must be built before adopted children can be moved into the property. If not, then both single beds and the associated dresser in the main hall must be built to move adopted children into the property.</li>\n<li>Leaving canopies off of the tower additions provides a full, unobstructed view and attack angles of the surrounding area and sky. The addition also functions normally (adding the exterior chest to the library creates a floating wall sconce), and characters will still utilize the towers in their daily activities.</li></ul>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260717014306\nCache expiry: 1209600\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.019 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.025 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 39/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 800/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 4/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nExtLoops count: 0/200\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    2.091      1 -total\n 78.48%    1.641     15 Template:G\n-->\n</div>"
